      "steps": [
        "Start the yellow rice first and cook it according to the package directions, since it will usually take longer than the taco filling.",
        "While the rice cooks, heat a large skillet over medium-high heat. Add the ground beef and break it up with a spatula.",
        "Cook the beef until no pink remains, about 6 to 8 minutes. Drain excess fat if needed.",
        "Add the taco seasoning from the kit and the amount of water called for on the package. Simmer until the beef is saucy but not watery.",
        "Warm the hard shells and soft tortillas according to the taco kit directions.",
        "Set out the beef, rice, shredded cheese, sour cream, and romaine separately so everyone can build tacos, rice bowls, or plain components."
      ],
