      "steps": [
        "Pat the chicken cutlets dry. If any pieces are thick, pound them to about 1/4 inch so they cook quickly and evenly.",
        "Season both sides with salt and pepper. Put the flour in a shallow bowl and lightly coat each cutlet, shaking off the excess.",
        "Heat olive oil and 1 tablespoon butter in a large skillet over medium-high heat until the butter foams.",
        "Sear the chicken in batches, about 2 to 3 minutes per side, until golden and just cooked through. Move cooked chicken to a plate.",
        "Lower the heat to medium. Add garlic and cook for about 30 seconds, just until fragrant.",
        "Add wine, if using, and scrape up the browned bits from the pan. Let it reduce for 1 to 2 minutes.",
        "Add chicken broth, lemon juice, and capers. Simmer for 3 to 5 minutes, until the sauce reduces slightly.",
        "Lower the heat and whisk in the cold butter a few pieces at a time until the sauce looks glossy.",
        "Return the chicken to the skillet and spoon sauce over it for 1 to 2 minutes.",
        "Finish with parsley and serve over pasta, rice, potatoes, or with a vegetable."
